<HEADLINE>
HOSPITAL CONFIRMS KAOHSIUNG MAYOR HAD LIGHT STROKE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung,  April 30 (CNA) 04/30/07  15:47:35 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
Kaohsiung Medical University Hospital (KMUH) confirmed Monday
that Kaohsiung Mayor Chen Chu has suffered a light stroke leaving
her right leg paralyzed and needing immediate rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
KMUH Vice President Lai Wen-teh made the confirmation at a press
conference at the hospital with Kaohsiung Deputy Mayor Chiu Tai-
san and City Director of Information Hsiao Yu-cheng.
</P>
<P>
Lai said Chen's blood pressure was still high since suffering a
stroke last week.
</P>
<P>
She was admitted to the KMUH last Thursday. On the Friday, she
still needed assistance getting out of bed because of dizziness
and motion dysfunction in her right leg, Lai said, noting the
hospital is trying to control her blood pressure.
</P>
<P>
Chiu said he will act for Chen while she is absent from work and
will attend ongoing question-and-answer sessions of the city
council on her behalf.
</P>
